  "prompt": "How do I have to pay the installments once I bought something through krazybee?",
  "response": "KrazyBee is a platform that offers microloans and financing options, particularly targeted at students for purchasing electronics, gadgets, and other items. If you've made a purchase through KrazyBee, here's a general outline of how you might manage your repayment process:\n\n1. **Installment Plan**: When you purchase an item, you agree to a specific installment plan, which outlines the amount and number of installments you will pay. \n\n2. **Payment Schedule**: You should receive a schedule detailing the due dates for each installment. It\u2019s crucial to pay attention to these dates to avoid late fees or penalties.\n\n3. **KrazyBee App/Website**: You can make your payments directly through the KrazyBee mobile app or website. Log into your account and navigate to the payments section to make a payment.\n\n4. **Payment Methods**: Payments can typically be made via various methods, including debit cards, credit cards, net banking, and UPI.\n\n5. **Notifications and Reminders**: KrazyBee usually sends reminders for due payments via SMS, email, or app notifications. Keep an eye on these to ensure you don't miss a payment.\n\n6. **Bank Account Linking**: Some repayment plans might involve setting up an auto-debit from your bank account, ensuring that the installment amount is automatically deducted on the due date.\n\n7. **Customer Support**: If you have any issues or need adjustments in your payment schedule, contact KrazyBee customer support for assistance.\n\nIt's important to read the terms and conditions of your loan agreement carefully to understand any associated fees, charges, or implications for late payment. If you're unsure about any aspect of your repayment, contacting KrazyBee's customer service is a good idea.",
